I think that you can do this without have_value. How about this?
do not assign value + have_value before the if statement
        if 'value' in kwargs:
            value = kwargs.pop('value')
        elif args:
            args = list(args)
            value = args.pop(0)
{{#defaultValue}}
        else:
            value = {{{defaultValue}}}
{{/defaultValue}}
{{^defaultValue}}
        else:
            raise ApiTypeError(
                "value is required, but not passed in args or kwargs and doesn't have default",
                path_to_item=_path_to_item,
                valid_classes=(self.__class__,),
            )
{{/defaultValue}}

My understanding is that all ModelSimple instances need an assigned value.

